  <text>
    <![CDATA[
    <p>
    The weather was ideal and the crowds were large for the 2017 Lone Star Rally in Galveston the weekend of November 4.
    </p>
    <p>
    The Strand is the main center of activity for the rally, serving as the cruising strip for bikes. There are numerous vendors of merchandise and food on the side streets, and at least one stage for bands. (The AC/DC tribute band "Highway to Hell" was really good.)
    </p>
    <p>
    A second activity center is along section of the Seawall near 25th Street, mainly featuring the larger motorcycle equipment vendors.
    </p>
    </p>
    ]]>
